# UI Guidelines

## Styling
- Use TailwindCSS as the primary styling approach for all components
- Use `class-variance-authority` (CVA) to define component variants
- Utilize the `cn` helper function (`@/utils/cn`) for combining and merging CSS classes
- Reference design tokens via CSS custom properties (`var(--*)`) instead of hardcoded values

## Accessibility
- Follow WAI-ARIA design patterns for all interactive elements
- Every interactive component must support keyboard navigation
- Use Radix UI primitives as the foundation for complex interactive components
- Include proper `aria-*` attributes where necessary

## Component Patterns
- Use `React.forwardRef` for all components that render a DOM element
- Support the `asChild` pattern via `@radix-ui/react-slot` where applicable
- Always accept and spread a `className` prop for consumer overrides
- Set `displayName` on every forwarded-ref component
